        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:38PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Lurleen State Park, or near Northport, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Tuscaloosa, Northport, Holt, Coker, Samantha, Lake Lurleen
State Park, Binion Creek Landing, Tuscaloosa Amphitheater, Tuscaloosa
Regional Airport, Bryant Denny Stadium, Lake Tuscaloosa, Lake
Tuscaloosa Dam, Flatwoods, Sexton Bend, University Of Alabama Quad,
Lake Harris, Tierce Pattton Bridge, Highway 69 Bridge, Oliver Lock
And Dam, and Lake Nicol.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
